      "side": 1,
      "message": "I also noticed that sign flip when I updated this. I believe it was a bug and I hadn\u0027t remembered that the fIH field could be negative 1/h instead of just 1/h (or 1 for texture rectangles).\n\nThe domain needs to be sorted since it\u0027s just used to provide the min and max values for clamping on u and v. Regardless of the origin of the texture, the domain needs to be inset so it should always go in by 1/2 texel.\n\nWe\u0027d only see the current buggy behavior if the texture was drawn with a domain strictly smaller than the vertical size of the texture, the texture had the bottom left origin (which I don\u0027t think is the default so that might be saving us...), and using bilerp filtering where the texture content 1px outside the intended domain actually has bad color data.",
